Calls a function with a reference to the contained value if [`Some`].

Returns the original option.

# Examples

```
let list = vec![1, 2, 3];

// prints "got: 2"
let x = list
    .get(1)
    .inspect(|x| println!("got: {x}"))
    .expect("list should be long enough");

// prints nothing
list.get(5).inspect(|x| println!("got: {x}"));
```
